I’ve wanted to get more experience writing programs that analyze programs, and after using Prisma schema I decided to try writing a program to convert a Python dataclass to a SQL schema.
At the time, I was starting up a project to extract and load Philadelphia city data into my own database. In the early stages of the project, I found myself toiling through “drop, recreate, rehydrate” cycles of rebuilding my tables and “rehydrating” my local db with test data.

